    • checkIsValidAdvancedInputs

      public java.lang.String checkIsValidAdvancedInputs()
      Returns a string of execution status. In general, the function checkIsValidAdvancedInputs returns "Success" if the inputs are valid, returns the corresponding execution status if the input(s) is(are) invalid.

      Two inputs and Three conditions are checked:

      • strMatePreference: whether it is empty.
      • strMateAcceptableYearOfDiff: whether it is larger than 0.
      • conditionOne: whether setAdvancedInput has been called in advance.
      • conditionTwo: whether checkIsValidSimpleInputs has been called in advance.
      • conditionThree: whether the year of birth range for the compatible pair mate is within 1880 to 2019.

      The function will be called by the function doMakePrediction in class Controller.

      Returns:
      the execution status, of String type.
